Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
loadDrc(25.10)                                                  loadDrc(25.10)

Name
       loadDrc  -  Loads  the  specified  Design Rule Checking (DRC) violation
       marker file

Syntax
       loadDrc

       [-help]

       <fileName>

       [-incremental]

       [-orient {r0 | r90 | r180 | r270 | mx | mx90 | my | my90}]

       [-origin <x y>]

       Loads the specified Design Rule Checking (DRC) violation  marker  file.
       Use  this  command  to  load DRC markers, which are saved in DB format,
       into Innovus design. The loadDrc command is useful in  situations  when
       you want to load DRC violation markers without having to load an entire
       design.

       For example, if during an Engineering Change Order (ECO), you find that
       only  25 of the 300 reported violations are actual violations that need
       to be corrected immediately, you can:

              * Delete the other 275 violations.

              * Save the 25 actual violations in a marker file using the save-
                Drc command.

              * Clear the violations from the design window.

              * Load the marker file containing the  saved  violation  markers
                using the loadDrc command.

       You can also use the loadDrc command in situations where, when correct-
       ing  violations, the ECO editor didn't make changes in the way that you
       want. Because the editor removed the marker when it  made  the  change,
       you  cannot  find the original violation in the design. You can use the
       loadDrc command to load the original marker file, then click on the vi-
       olation, and zoom to the area in which you are working on.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each loadDrc parameter.

              For  a  detailed  description of the command and all its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man loadDrc

       <fileName>
              Specifies the name of the marker file to be loaded.

       -incremental
              Loads the markers stored in the  specified  file  incrementally.
              This  means  that  the markers that are already loaded in memory
              will not be removed before new ones are loaded from  the  speci-
              fied file.

       -orient {r0 | r90 | r180 | r270 | mx | mx90 | my | my90}
              Rotates all the DRCs available in the violation marker file with
              the specified orientation.

       -origin <x y>
              Specifies the origin coordinate of the DRC available in the vio-
              lation marker file.

Example
       The  following  command loads markers that were previously saved to the
       VG.drc file using saveDrc:

       loadDrc VG.drc

